cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DC

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Natural Language Processing tasks and specifically focuses on BERT models.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel method for quantizing BERT models using second order Hessian information.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions visualization techniques used to analyze the Hessian information.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper deals with state-of-the-art models used for NLP tasks and proposes a new method for compressing these models.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the challenge of deploying BERT models in resource-constrained environments.
